Hi.

1. Remove the photo;

2. Add Czech Republic to Prague if you are looking for work outside of the Czech Republic (not everyone knows what it is and where it is);

3. Profile → Summary;

4. The summary is about motivation, it resembles more of a diary. This section is called summary for a reason; it should contain a digest of your experience (you can enhance it with motivation, but that's not the main thing);

5. Natural languages definitely shouldn’t be at the top of the skills list. I would definitely remove flags: firstly, it's bias in the current situation, secondly, more than 10 countries speak Russian.

Here’s how I would do it:

• Name | Title | Contacts | Links
• Summary
• Experience
• Skills

• Describe work experience in 3-4 concise bullet points, no more. In your case, you need to merge the bullets from the first resume with the text description from the second.

• Add location and product to companies;

• It's meaningful to list technologies in separate positions if they significantly differ (usually mobile developers have hundreds of technologies), if it's all roughly the same, it’s better to keep it in skills or spread it across the bullets;

The main rule here — the resume must be ATS-friendly.

From the option "with design" you can take some parts from experience and skills (without languages).

Experience needs to be polished in terms of typography — gray, italic, small text on a white background is torture for the recruiter. It should be comfortable for him to read (scan) the text, and the formatting should help with that and not hinder it.

How you rearrange it — send for a re-review 🔥
